    <p>
      We are a Low Power FM (LPFM) non-commercial DIY radio station broadcasting on <b>KHUH 104.9 FM</b> and online from a public space in Seattle's Central District.
      We are also an all-ages music and performance venue. Our focus is on audio not often heard on the traditional radio dial, including: found sound, field recordings, forgotten music, local musicians, bedroom recordings, lo-fi demos, dreams, storytelling, conversations from within marginalized communities and <em>things that feel real</em>.
We acknowledge and celebrate raw talent and imperfections, and encourage emerging artists to take a chance with us.
We support local and NW music and other underground music from around the world.
